---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Uses — Rui André Batista"
  description="Hardware, software, and tools I use daily as a blind software engineer."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>
      <span class="prefix" aria-hidden="true">~/</span>uses
    </h1>
    <p>What I use to get work done.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="uses-content">
    <section aria-labelledby="screen-readers-heading">
      <h2 id="screen-readers-heading">Screen Readers</h2>
      <dl class="uses-list">
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>NVDA</dt>
          <dd>Primary screen reader on Windows. Free, open source, and the one I contributed to for years.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>VoiceOver</dt>
          <dd>Built into macOS and iOS. My go-to on Apple devices.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>Orca</dt>
          <dd>Screen reader for Linux/GNOME.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="hardware-heading">
      <h2 id="hardware-heading">Hardware</h2>
      <dl class="uses-list">
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>Braille display</dt>
          <dd>Essential for reading code, reviewing formatting, and anything where audio isn't precise enough. I use a refreshable braille display connected via USB or Bluetooth.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>Standard keyboard</dt>
          <dd>No mouse. Everything is keyboard-driven.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="dev-tools-heading">
      <h2 id="dev-tools-heading">Development</h2>
      <dl class="uses-list">
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>Terminal</dt>
          <dd>Where most of my work happens. Git, build tools, SSH — all keyboard, all accessible.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>VS Code</dt>
          <dd>Good screen reader support, decent with NVDA and VoiceOver.</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="uses-item">
          <dt>IntelliJ IDEA</dt>
          <dd>For JVM work (Scala, Java, Kotlin). Accessibility has improved over the years.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <p class="note">
      This page is a work in progress. I'll expand it over time.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .prefix {
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .page-header p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-block-start: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .uses-content {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .uses-content section {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    padding-block-end: var(--space-sm);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .uses-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .uses-item dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .uses-item dd {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .note {
    margin-block-start: var(--space-2xl);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border: 1px dashed var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
